      "notes": "Gold flowchart animation. The six phases reveal in sequence with connecting arrows drawing in (stroke-dashoffset) and labels appearing as each segment finishes — the staged reveal teaches the strict one-direction order far better than a static image. Self-contained inline SVG/CSS/JS and a prefers-reduced-motion fallback. technical_validity is 9 (not 10) because ids/classes are scoped with a concept prefix (a-/b-/h-/blk-) rather than the image_id itself — a perfect 10 would prefix every id/class with the image_id so multiple animations never collide."
